sentences: Delia Micucci Valeri (October 4, 1870 – January 27, 1947) was an American vocal coach, born in Italy.
She moved to the United States before 1901.
She worked with African-American soprano Florence Cole Talbert in Italy in the 1920s.
In 1942 Valeri opened a studio in Hollywood.
Delia Micucci married August Valeri in New York City about 1901.
